INSERT INTO `news` VALUES (21,1045,'2010-12-02','AGD Donates to Ronald McDonald House of San Francisco','Service to the Community',NULL,'<p>We should all do our part. With so much going on around us&mdash;work,  deadlines, talks of a stale economy&ndash;it&rsquo;s rather easy to forget to  appreciate what we do have.</p>','<p>We should all do our part. With so much going on around us&mdash;work, deadlines, talks of a stale economy&ndash;it&rsquo;s rather easy to forget to appreciate what we do have. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nAs a pledge to give back to our community, AG Design Group selected Ronald McDonald House of San Francisco for our 2010 annual donation recipient. What a better way to give thanks and appreciation for the success we saw in the past year. Let&rsquo;s all &ldquo;pay it forward&rdquo;!</p>','news__20110505131927.jpg',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,'2011-05-18 20:30:58','2010-12-17 16:40:55'),(20,1045,'2011-02-08','Marketing in 2011 & Beyond: 5 Myths Dispelled','5 Myths','Arlene Santos','<p>Today the Internet, social networks, TV, mobile  phone applications, and digital airwaves make everything so confusing.  Which is better? Which will provide better exposure and profit for my  company? Find out here.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p>We are often lead to believe that more and bigger, is better. However is this era of gizmos and gadgets, more is much more daunting than the simplicity of the past. Previously, the media consisted of the TV, radio, print publications and the mail. Today the Internet, social networks, satellite TV, cable TV, mobile phone applications, and digital airwaves make everything so confusing. This makes things really confusing for small business owners who want to advertise but don\\\'t know where to begin. Which is better? Which will provide better exposure and profit for my company? More, certainly have people more perplexed.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>AGD helps to unravel some myths surrounding advertising, marketing and the many options available to them.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Myth #1 &ndash; <b>In order to get through to people I have to bombard them using every outlet available.</b>&nbsp;Effective and smart advertising should never &ldquo;bombard&rdquo; anyone. Effective advertising should be intelligent, memorable and compelling. It is not necessary to use every media outlet available. Not only is this a lofty task, but a very expensive one. In order to decide which avenue is best for your business you must understand your consumer. If your consumers are primarily the elderly, chances are that advertising on You Tube will not be that effective.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Myth #2 &ndash; <b>Consumers are so heavily inundated by the media that they have become immune to marketing.</b> If marketing did not work, corporate entities would not spend billions of dollars annually on advertising. While it is true that consumers do prefer to fast-forward through commercials or invest in items that profess to have less commercial breaks, marketing certainly does have an impact. The key to standing out amongst all the noise is establishing an effective strategy. Advertise where your patrons are likely to see you. If the majority of your clientele are teenagers, Facebook and You Tube would be better advertising options than the New York Times. Once you have chosen the best avenues to reach your clientele, make sure you develop an intelligent ad campaign that is sure to catch their eye. For example, if you are targeting seniors, it is not a good idea to use small font, lots of jargon and loud colors. The key is to speak to your audience.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Myth #3 &ndash; <b>If I have an ad displayed in a high traffic area such as a TV commercial, Google, etc., it will bring my company business.</b>&nbsp;Simply having an ad presence does not guarantee business. Where is your ad located? What does it look like? What does it say? Do your consumers use Google?&nbsp;Placement, positions, size, design and content are factors in the effectiveness of your ad campaign as well as where you choose to advertise. So you got an ad on TV, now what? Does your target market watch TV or the channel you have the commercial placed on? What about the programming during your ad? Smart advertising is not just simply making an appearance on &ldquo;the big screen&rdquo;.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Myth #4 &ndash; <b>My business can survive using &ldquo;free&rdquo; advertising.</b> Many small businesses choose not to advertise because they feel that with all the rage in social networks and hubs, they can get away with &ldquo;free&rdquo; marketing. While having a presence on Facebook, Yelp, Twitter, Google, may do some to get your name out there, it is not very effective as an advertising mechanism. A Facebook page does not guarantee a spike in business and setting up a business profile on Yelp will not ensure great reviews.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Myth #5 &ndash; <b>My Company is too small to embark on an advertising campaign.</b> No company is too small to advertise. Many small companies shy away from advertising because of the cost and because they are unsure of where to advertise. Marketing does not need to be a huge expenditure. Marketing takes on many forms and could be as simple as sending out a holiday card with a discount offer to your current customer base. Regardless of the size of your budget or company, marketing can be as simple or complicated as you would like it to be. Effective marketing will ensure your company&rsquo;s growth and success.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','news__20110505131317.jpg',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,'2011-05-26 16:21:59','2010-12-17 15:55:49'),(29,1045,'2011-03-08','New Website for Professional Massage Therapy','New Website',NULL,'<p>AGD designs website for local massage therapists.</p>','<p><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt;\\\">Walnut Creek, CA - AG Design Group Inc., a graphic design and marketing firm specializing in branding, has developed a new website for Walnut Creek based massage spa, Professional Massage Therapy. Known for their elegant, custom designs, AG Design Group developed a site for Professional Massage Therapy that is attractive and functional. </span></p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt;\\\">AG Design Group is a leader in their industry. Specializing is graphic design, their custom developed logos and print collateral have won they several accolades and awards. Their user friendly website applications have made it easy on their clients to update and edit their site on their own. &ldquo;There are a lot of templates available to clients when in comes to graphic art, website content management tools and eCommerce sites,&rdquo; says Perlita Herrera, Communications Manager at AG Design Group. &ldquo;What we offer is custom designs and solutions that not only set companies apart, but helps facilitate their business in a way that makes sense for each individual client. No two clients are the same. So why should their marketing material and operating systems function the same?&rdquo; </span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt;\\\">Recently, AG Design Group has launched a website for Walnut Creek-based massage professionals, Professional Massage Therapy. Consistent with their branding, also developed by AG Design Group, the site is simple, stylish and professional. The user-friendly interface allows users to easily find information and content. To view the site visit <a href=\\\"http://www.professionalmassagetherapywc.com/\\\">www.ProfessionalMassageTherapyWC.com</a></span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','news__20110630123902.jpg',NULL,NULL,1,'on','2011-06-30 11:39:06','2011-06-30 11:16:26'),(25,1045,'2011-02-01','3 Things You Should Know About Branding and Marketing','3 Things to Know',NULL,'<p>Not all branding is created equal. Simply having a logo does not necessarily ensure proper branding, and can do more harm than good. These are three things all business owners should know about their brand.</p>','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt;\\\">Branding is a crucial must in today&rsquo;s business climate. Creating a business image and company identity is what sets businesses apart. While most business owners realize the importance of this pivotal step, some take the task lightly.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt;\\\">Not all branding is created equal. Simply having a logo does not necessarily ensure proper branding, and can do more harm than good. These are three things all business owners should know about their brand:</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt;\\\">1.&nbsp;<b>Your Brand Should Target Your Ideal Clientele</b>: In the marketing industry, there is much ado about targeting a specific audience, reaching your consumers, and speaking to certain demographics. While this may be true, branding should speak to the clientele you wish to attract. If you wish to service big corporations or large companies, but are currently servicing small businesses, your branding should speak to corporate executives and reflect the caliber of a company they would likely work with. Working with a trained firm can give you insight into your audience&rsquo;s buying habits, likes, dislikes and psychological graphs. Understanding your ideal client is essential when developing a successful brand. </span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt;\\\">2. <b>Your Brand Reflects The Way You Conduct Business</b>: Your brand (logo, brochures, website, etc.) provides insight into your business operation and how you conduct business. The old adage, dress for success, could not ring any truer. Branding is the clothes one wears to the interview. Those who are rough around the edges rarely get hired for the VP position. If your company has a thrifty appearance or templated branding, then you attract clients who are expecting discount prices. Clients never walk into Starbucks and negotiate the price for a cup of coffee or ask for a discount on a bagel.&nbsp;In order to avoid this, your branding should reflect the goals of your company, who you hope to become and give the impression that you&rsquo;re established, credible and here to stay.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt;\\\">3. <b>Even The Best Branding Needs Marketing Strategy</b>: A good brand starts with a good logo that is applied consistently and constantly. However, even the best branding will not get your phone to ring. Simply having a stellar website and an artfully designed brochure will not generate business. Effective branding needs to be accompanied by an effective marketing strategy. Branding is simply the foundation from which to build upon. </span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt;\\\">AG Design Group Inc. has been creating successful brands and marketing strategies since 2006. Our team combines over 30 years of experience in print, logo and website development for various industries. This February we are offering a complimentary brand assessment. Have your brand evaluated and walk away with tips to improve your business. Also visit us on <a href=\\\"http://www.facebook.com/agdesigngroup\\\">Facebook</a> to view our current projects and get valuable tips on branding. Remember, <b><i>branding without strategy is just a bunch of pictures</i></b>.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,'perlita@agdesigngroup.net',NULL,'on','2011-05-18 20:29:26','2011-01-28 18:59:18'),(22,1045,'2010-12-31','AGD @ A New Year, A New You','AGD @ Tradeshow',NULL,'<p>&nbsp;AGD helps client design and operate a trade show booth at event.</p>','<p><span style=\\\"\\\">Brentwood, CA - A New Year, A New You, a Brentwood event focused on helping people&nbsp;develop a better, healthier you in the coming year, is probably a great place to seek fitness advice. This year, you can also find Bill Schaaf, franchise owner of California Document Preparers. &ldquo;Our goal is to get people to start thinking about their future,&rdquo; explains Schaaf. &ldquo; A Living Trust is extremely important in making end of life decisions official. A new you should start with safeguarding your future.&rdquo; Helping operate his booth at this years trade show is local graphic design firm, AG Design Group Inc.</span></p>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt;\\\">California Document Preparers are <strong><span style=\\\"font-weight: normal;\\\">Legal Document Assistants (LDA)</span></strong> who specialize in assisting people who wish to represent themselves in uncontested legal matters.&nbsp; They provide an <strong><span style=\\\"font-weight: normal;\\\">affordable </span></strong>alternative to traditional legal services. Cal Docs most popular forms are divorce, living trusts, probate and deeds. &ldquo;What makes us different from online vendors,&rdquo; explains Schaaf, &ldquo;is that we are real people guiding you through the entire process. We also make it easy by filing all forms for you.&rdquo; </span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt;\\\">AG Design Group Inc., a Walnut Creek based graphic design and marketing firm, is the architect behind California Document Preparers&rsquo; brand and marketing campaign. This year, AG Design Group took the extra step to manage California Document Preparers tradeshow displays and booth. &ldquo;We are committed to helping our clients succeed in every facet of their business,&rdquo; states Perlita Herrera, Communications Manager at AG Design Group. &ldquo;We truly believe that Cal Docs provides a much needed service and are happy to develop their branding further than just a logo. Ultimately their success is ours.&rdquo;</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt;\\\">Schaaf recognizes that most people find organizing their living trust or planning an Advanced Health Care Directive daunting and easy to procrastinate. He hopes to reach out to people who are ready to turn a new leaf this new year, at the event. Herrera agrees, &ldquo;Part of developing a new you is to face challenges previously though difficult and addressing matters that are easy to put off. &ldquo;&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt;\\\">The event will be held at the Delta Athletic Club in Brentwood on Saturday, January 8. For more information visit www.sellitevents.com.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt;\\\">To learn more about California Document Preparers and how they can help you, visit <a href=\\\"http://www.CaDocPreparers.com\\\">www.CaDocPreparers.com</a>.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'on','2011-05-18 20:29:03','2010-12-21 12:38:55'),(23,1045,'2011-02-01','AG Design Group, Re-designs a Singles Social Introduction Website','Just Launched',NULL,'<p>AGD launches matching-making website, MatchesThatMatter.com</p>','<p><!--[if !mso]>\r\n<style>\r\nv\\\\:* {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\r\no\\\\:* {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\r\nw\\\\:* {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\r\n.shape {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n<w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\\\"false\\\" DefUnhideWhenUsed=\\\"true\\\"\r\nDefSemiHidden=\\\"true\\\" DefQFormat=\\\"false\\\" DefPriority=\\\"99\\\"\r\nLatentStyleCount=\\\"267\\\">\r\n<w:LsdException Locked=\\\"false\\\" Priority=\\\"0\\\" SemiHidden=\\\"false\\\"\r\nUnhideWhenUsed=\\\"false\\\" QFormat=\\\"true\\\" Name=\\\"Normal\\\" />\r\n<w:LsdException Locked=\\\"false\\\" Priority=\\\"9\\\" SemiHidden=\\\"false\\\"\r\nUnhideWhenUsed=\\\"false\\\" QFormat=\\\"true\\\" Name=\\\"heading 1\\\" />\r\n<w:LsdException Locked=\\\"false\\\" Pr