\"false\\\"\r\nUnhideWhenUsed=\\\"false\\\" Name=\\\"Dark List Accent 6\\\" />\r\n<w:LsdException Locked=\\\"false\\\" Priority=\\\"71\\\" SemiHidden=\\\"false\\\"\r\nUnhideWhenUsed=\\\"false\\\" Name=\\\"Colorful Shading Accent 6\\\" />\r\n<w:LsdException Locked=\\\"false\\\" Priority=\\\"72\\\" SemiHidden=\\\"false\\\"\r\nUnhideWhenUsed=\\\"false\\\" Name=\\\"Colorful List Accent 6\\\" />\r\n<w:LsdException Locked=\\\"false\\\" Priority=\\\"73\\\" SemiHidden=\\\"false\\\"\r\nUnhideWhenUsed=\\\"false\\\" Name=\\\"Colorful Grid Accent 6\\\" />\r\n<w:LsdException Locked=\\\"false\\\" Priority=\\\"19\\\" SemiHidden=\\\"false\\\"\r\nUnhideWhenUsed=\\\"false\\\" QFormat=\\\"true\\\" Name=\\\"Subtle Emphasis\\\" />\r\n<w:LsdException Locked=\\\"false\\\" Priority=\\\"21\\\" SemiHidden=\\\"false\\\"\r\nUnhideWhenUsed=\\\"false\\\" QFormat=\\\"true\\\" Name=\\\"Intense Emphasis\\\" />\r\n<w:LsdException Locked=\\\"false\\\" Priority=\\\"31\\\" SemiHidden=\\\"false\\\"\r\nUnhideWhenUsed=\\\"false\\\" QFormat=\\\"true\\\" Name=\\\"Subtle Reference\\\" />\r\n<w:LsdException Locked=\\\"false\\\" Priority=\\\"32\\\" SemiHidden=\\\"false\\\"\r\nUnhideWhenUsed=\\\"false\\\" QFormat=\\\"true\\\" Name=\\\"Intense Reference\\\" />\r\n<w:LsdException Locked=\\\"false\\\" Priority=\\\"33\\\" SemiHidden=\\\"false\\\"\r\nUnhideWhenUsed=\\\"false\\\" QFormat=\\\"true\\\" Name=\\\"Book Title\\\" />\r\n<w:LsdException Locked=\\\"false\\\" Priority=\\\"37\\\" Name=\\\"Bibliography\\\" />\r\n<w:LsdException Locked=\\\"false\\\" Priority=\\\"39\\\" QFormat=\\\"true\\\" Name=\\\"TOC Heading\\\" />\r\n</w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n/* Style Definitions */\r\ntable.MsoNormalTable\r\n{mso-style-name:\\\"Table Normal\\\";\r\nmso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\nmso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\nmso-style-noshow:yes;\r\nmso-style-priority:99;\r\nmso-style-qformat:yes;\r\nmso-style-parent:\\\"\\\";\r\nmso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;\r\nmso-para-margin:0in;\r\nmso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\nfont-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\\\"Times New Roman\\\",\\\"serif\\\";}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--></p>\r\n<div style=\\\"text-align: left; \\\">\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;\\\">Oakland, CA &ndash; AG Design Group, an award winning graphic design and marketing firm that specializes in branding and website development, recently launched a new website for their client Matches That Matter. Oakland based Matches That Matter has introduced a different style of match making. Matches That Matter pairs compatible singles into groups who participate in community outreach activities. Singles can get to know each other while contributing something positive to the community. </span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;\\\">AG Design Group has gained much notoriety in its field for its custom design styles, user interface, dynamic user experience and highly effective Content Management Systems. &ldquo;It is important that your main point of contact with your clients, your website, reflects your business perfectly.&rdquo; states Perlita Herrera, Communications Manager at AG Design Group. &ldquo;We believe that Matches That Matter&rsquo;s match&ndash;making strategy is truly unique. Our goal with this site was to develop a look and style that visually set Matches That Matter apart from other dating sites.&rdquo;</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;\\\">In order to draw the distinction between the Matches That Matter dating strategy versus conventional dating sites, AG Design Group developed a more personable user experience. The new design incorporates an easy, clear navigation and warm, inviting feel. &ldquo;It was really important to us that we work with an experienced firm,&rdquo; notes Odette Pollar, Founder and CEO of Matches That Matter. &ldquo;The staff at AG Design are professionals. We could rest assured knowing that design and development were being attended to, so that we could focus our energy on our clients.&rdquo; </span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;\\\">Complete with a sleek color scheme, interactive dating game and a custom-developed Content Management System, AG Design has hit the mark with new Matches That Matter site.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;\\\">Matches That Matter currently serves singles over 40 in the San Francisco Bay Area. With their newly re-designed website they hope to expand their services to include the entire coast of California by the end of 2011.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n</div>','news__20110505131740.jpg',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,'2011-02-08 11:58:37','2010-12-21 12:54:28'),(24,1045,'2011-01-28','New Office and Website for AG Design Group Inc','New in 2011',NULL,'<p>AGD gets moves to a more spacious office and gets a web facelift!!</p>','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt;\\\">This new year, AG Design Group Inc., a Walnut Creek based graphic design and marketing firm, has much to celebrate. Their very busy 2010 has triggered another growth spurt. To celebrate and accommodate their growth, AG Design Group has moved offices and launched a re-designed website. </span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt;\\\">After working on several re-design&rsquo;s for clients, AG Design decided they too needed to upgrade their look and refresh their material. To commemorate the beginning of a new year, AG Design Group has launched their re-designed website. The design was treated with a more modern and jovial approach. The site also features recent projects, project samples and case studies. Follow them on <a href=\\\"http://www.facebook.com/agdesigngroup\\\">Facebook</a> to keep up with their latest activity and get insightful design and marketing tips.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt;\\\">In addition to a renovated website, AG Design Group has added several new faces to the team. To accommodate their growing staff, AG Design Group has moved to a larger office. Although they remain in the same office building, the new office is much more spacious. Visit the <a href=\\\"http://agdesigngroup.net/page_ppl.php?page_id=1043\\\">Team</a> page, to learn about the new staff members.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','news__20110208111822.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,'on','2011-05-18 20:29:12','2011-01-28 18:53:19'),(30,1045,'2011-08-04','SEO Tid-Bit No.1','SEO','Arlene Santos','<p>Did you know that page loading time affects your Search Engine Ranking? With so many web surfers looking for quick answers, web pages that have painstaking load times, may find themselves sinking lower and lower in the Google ranking.</p>','<p>Did you know that page loading time affects your Search Engine Ranking?</p>\r\n<p>If it\\\'s not hard enough to achieve good SEO ranking, Google has added another element to the equation. Last Spring, Goggle announced that page speed, or how quickly your web page loads, plays a role in web search ranking. Although at this point it doesn\\\'t affect your SEO ranking too much, don\\\'t be surprised if this criteria becomes more important in the near future. With so many web surfers looking for quick answers, web pages that have painstaking load times, may find themselves sinking lower and lower in the Google ranking.</p>\r\n<p>So what does this mean? Older sites that were coded using out-dated practices (like slices of background images) or some WordPress sites with slow load times will need to be recoded. Remember sites should have a shelf life of about 4-5 years before needing to update &mdash; not just the look or design, but in most cases, the programming and underlying code base.</p>','news__20110914150454.jpg',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,'2011-09-14 14:13:11','2011-08-04 17:33:14'),(31,1045,'2011-09-08','UC Berkeley Website Redesign','UC Berkeley Website Redesign','Perlita Herrera','<p>AG Design Group Inc., a local graphic design and website development  firm, recently launched a new website for UC Berkeley&rsquo;s Rhetoric  Department.</p>','<p><i>Sep 08, 2011</i> - Berkeley, CA &ndash; AG Design Group Inc., a local  graphic design and website development firm with a solid reputation for  developing custom website designs and databases, recently launched a new  website for UC Berkeley&rsquo;s Rhetoric Department. The UC Berkeley Rhetoric  Department offers a premiere graduate and post-graduate program.  Recently, the Rhetoric Department decided to update their website, and  sought out AG Design Group as their premiere choice. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;It is  important for universities to stay on top of emerging technologies to  help streamline their registration processes,&rdquo; say Arlene Santos,  founder and Creative Director at AG Design Group. &ldquo;Most academic  organizations shy away from upgrading their system, but with our  comprehensive database technology, the transition can be accomplished  within a reasonable amount of time, while also enhancing website  usability and aesthetics. We were excited to have worked with UC  Berkeley and look forward to working with more of their departments in  the future.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>To read the full article, please click here: <a href=\\\"http://www.prlog.org/11652900-uc-berkeley-rhetoric-department-gets-new-website.html\\\">http://www.prlog.org/11652900-uc-berkeley-rhetoric-department-gets-new-website.html</a></p>','news__20110914151015.jpg',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,'2011-09-14 14:13:00','2011-09-14 14:09:46');
